;W[rs]LB[sr:1][sq:2][rs:3]C[Dia.2 Black takes first

The 2,1 point sure is popular today.  In this case it's the right move and gets the Pae started.  White will dansu at 3 and now Black must fight White for control of the corner.  This is the right idea but not correct because Black takes the Pae first, so White has to look for the first Pae threat.
\lang1042\f1\fs18
